T*
(6. Metadata-Driven Pattern \(Core of this POC\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(6.1 What â€śmetadata-drivenâ€ť means here) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The pipeline does not hardcode source connection options in the ingest) Tj
T*
(step. Instead, SetupMetadata writes a metadata row into metadata_config,) Tj
T*
(and IngestBronze reads that active row at runtime.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Operationally:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(-   control plane = metadata + rules tables) Tj
T*
(-   execution plane = Spark steps consuming control metadata) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(6.2 Metadata-Driven Execution Flow) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(    SetupMetadata) Tj
T*
(      -> write metadata_config \(source_format, source_options, target_table\)) Tj
T*
(      -> write dq_rules) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(    IngestBronze) Tj
T*
(      -> read active row from metadata_config) Tj
T*
(      -> resolve source format/options dynamically) Tj
T*
(      -> load data and write Bronze) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(6.3 Why this is valuable) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(-   decouples pipeline logic from environment-specific source details) Tj
T*
(-   supports controlled source changes without code rewrite) Tj
T*
(-   enables reusable ingestion step for additional sources) Tj
T*
(-   centralizes rule governance in dq_rules) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(6.4 Current POC Boundaries) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(-   single active source: customers_mongo) Tj
T*
(-   single domain table pair: bronze_customers -> silver_customers) Tj
T*
(-   rule execution currently tied to current Silver records) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
